[2025-07-19 21:53:28] [INFO] my_app_logger: [Document(metadata={'version': 'unknown', 'text': None, 'effective_date': '2025-07-19', 'source': 'moaaz resume.pdf', 'page': 0.0, 'doc_id': 'moaaz resume'}, page_content='Moaaz Siddiqui\nGulshan Iqbal, Karachi\n♂phone0318-2553857 /envel⌢pemoaaz7151@gmail.com /linkedinlinkedin.com/in /githubgithub.com/moaaz12-web\nSummary\nA software engineering graduate with a strong foundation in AI, NLP, CV, and Python development. My journey\nhas included hands-on experience with large language models (LLMs), AI-powered solutions, and seamless backend\nintegrations.\nEducation\nNED University of Engineering and Technology Oct. 2020 – July 2024\nBachelor of Science in Software Engineering - GPA: 3.50 Karachi, Sindh\nExperience\nGaditek December 2024 – Present\nAssociate Software Engineer - AI Karachi, Pakistan\n• Worked on AI-based backend tools for interview preparation, candidate CV customization, and job description\ngeneration for recruiters using FastAPI\n• Researched and implemented an agentic Langgraph-based workflow that takes user query and automatically performs all\nactions like a human.'), Document(metadata={'version': 'unknown', 'text': None, 'effective_date': '2025-07-19', 'source': 'moaaz resume.pdf', 'page': 0.0, 'doc_id': 'moaaz resume'}, page_content='generation for recruiters using FastAPI\n• Researched and implemented an agentic Langgraph-based workflow that takes user query and automatically performs all\nactions like a human.\n• Created a recommendation algorithm for recruiters, where they can post a job description and get recommended\ncandidates for that job description\nDevelopers World LLC March 2023 – Jume 2024\nAI Engineer Remote, USA\n• Fine-tuned Mistral LLM using supervised fine tuning (SFT) for rating question answer pairs. Manually crafted the\ndataset by myself.\n• Developed a multilingual AI pipeline with ChatGPT API, OpenAI Whisper, and Roberta for multilingual QA, with web\nsearch and summarization\n• Fine-tuned and deployed transformer models on Amazon SageMaker for hate speech detection, utilizing secure S3 storage\nand an API endpoint.\n• Applied AWS Textract for OCR on receipt data, fine-tuned LayoutlmV3 on the OCR results using Amazon SageMaker,\nand deployed the model on HuggingFace inference API.\nProjects'), Document(metadata={'version': 'unknown', 'text': None, 'effective_date': '2025-07-19', 'source': 'moaaz resume.pdf', 'page': 0.0, 'doc_id': 'moaaz resume'}, page_content='and an API endpoint.\n• Applied AWS Textract for OCR on receipt data, fine-tuned LayoutlmV3 on the OCR results using Amazon SageMaker,\nand deployed the model on HuggingFace inference API.\nProjects\nAdvanced RAG application| Python, LangChain, HuggingFac, Streamlit Code\n• Built a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) application with Langchain for document question answering.\n• Utilized advanced RAG techniques like multi-query retriever, reranking, and semantic chunking for improved\nperformance\n• Leveraged transformer models for llm and text embeddings, and Streamlit for creating an interface\nAutomatic Number Plate recognition| Python, YOLOv8, OpenCV, Tkinter, EasyOCR Code | Demo\n• Created a Tkinter application for tracking cars in real time and their license plates.\n• Used pretrained YOLOv8 model for car detection and fine-tuned YOLOv8 model for license plate detection\n• Leveraged SORT tracker for real-time car tracking and EasyOCR for extracting license plate text.'), Document(metadata={'version': 'unknown', 'text': None, 'effective_date': '2025-07-19', 'source': 'moaaz resume.pdf', 'page': 0.0, 'doc_id': 'moaaz resume'}, page_content='• Leveraged SORT tracker for real-time car tracking and EasyOCR for extracting license plate text.\nChatbot with per-user retrieval| Python, Langchain, FastAPI, Redis Code\n• Created a Langchain-based chatbot with per-user memory retrieval, using Redis as the vector database for storing users’\nconversations. Utilized transformer models and LLMs for text embedding and conversing with the user.\n• Developed the backend with FastAPI and Langserve, and dockerized the entire application using Docker. The final\nproduct includes two API endpoints: one for changing the user and the other for chatting with the chatbot.\nTechnical Skills\nLanguages: Python, SQL, C++\nTechnologies/Frameworks: Numpy, Pandas, Plotly, Seaborn, Tensorflow, Keras, PyTorch, Transformers, Langchain,\nLlamaIndex, Transformers, Diffusion models, MongoDB, Neo4J, Streamlit\nExtracurricular\n• Winner of ITEC 22, Data Science Competition, 2022 - Winner of the university-level data science competition ITEC,'), Document(metadata={'version': 'unknown', 'text': None, 'effective_date': '2025-07-19', 'source': 'moaaz resume.pdf', 'page': 0.0, 'doc_id': 'moaaz resume'}, page_content='Extracurricular\n• Winner of ITEC 22, Data Science Competition, 2022 - Winner of the university-level data science competition ITEC,\norganized by ACM-NEDUET. More than 15 teams from different universities participated in this competition.\n• Runner up in Envision Data Science Competition, 2023')]
